The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to better predict human behavior, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on cognitive modeling and understanding human decision-making suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the mention of a dataset and data-driven approach suggests a connection to cybernetics (cs.CY).
